tip.text: A small lounge and no spa, but the service is excellent and the dinner was nice as well.

A good deal for Portland. Location a bit far from bars and restaurants. Nice & comfy, but as the building is old, it has its downsides. Our bathroom was across the hall in a separate (private) room.
Recommended! One of the best meals I had in NE. Poutine, duckfat fries, meatloaf panino, beer & cheese soup... Everything was spectacular! Also very good craft beers and excellent, friendly service.

tip.text: Great Peruvian food and cocktails! Ceviche, empanadas and quinotto (quinoa prepared like risotto) were excellent. Very good service and a stylish setting. Recommended!
A lovely restaurant by the sea. Ask to be seated outside if the weather is nice. Good food, very good service.
